The article pays tribute to John Warner, highlighting his extraordinary life of service and accomplishment. It mentions his enlistment in the Navy at a young age, his service with the Marines in the Korean War, his time as Secretary of the Navy, and his five terms in the United States Senate. The author, who served alongside Warner in the Senate for three decades, describes him as someone guided by his conscience and the Constitution. Warner was known for staying true to his convictions and values, even if it meant going against his party's position. The article also mentions how Warner supported the author in the 2020 election, crossing party lines. It concludes by referencing a poem that Warner requested to be read into the Senate Record upon his departure from the Senate, symbolizing his role in guiding the "ship of state." The article expresses condolences to Warner's family.